 Deji Elumoye in Abuja President Muhammadu Buhari has mourned the demise of the longest-serving Zamfara monarch, Emir of Kwatarkwashi in Bungudu Local Government Area of the state, Alhaji Ahmad Umar, describing the death as “a void that cannot be filled.” President Buhari in a release issued yesterday by his spokesman, Mallam Garba Shehu, said “a kind and caring ruler has left us.” According to him, the 61 years of the deceased on the throne had witnessed the growth and development of his community, for which succeeding generations will continue to appreciate him. The President prayed for the repose of the soul of the deceased and urged the people of Kwatarkwashi kingdom and Zamfara State in general to bear the loss with fortitude.